"It's a great honour to meet a wizard as powerful as you," he said. "Would you mind sharing with me the secret of your magic?" The young man smiled and said, "My friend, I'm not a wizard. I'm a teacher. What I wrote on those parchments were not magic utterances, but polite words. The first word was 'please' and the second was 'thank you'. What our king lacked were good manners. Even though he was a just king, he didn't speak to his people politely. That's why his people disobeyed his orders. These polite words will turn any command into a kind, polite request."
